{"id": "EUVD-2022-54980", "enisaUuid": "f7cbde39-004b-3449-bb0e-966493d5590b", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nASoC: atmel: Fix error handling in snd_proto_probe\n\nThe device_node pointer is returned by of_parse_phandle()  with refcount\nincremented. We should use of_node_put() on it when done.\n\nThis function only calls of_node_put() in the regular path.\nAnd it will cause refcount leak in error paths.\nFix this by calling of_node_put() in error handling too.", "datePublished": "2025-09-22T21:30:15", "dateUpdated": "2025-09-22T21:30:15", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f32ac9bf5e3f594ef9bfedb410aebc98cf784e69", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0f517480d5888cd54487c5662ce4da95b30ad798", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8fa969cd8485031294f91fc7184399000cae6355", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b0bfaf0544d08d093d6211d7ef8816fb0b5b6c75", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49246"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49246"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "00884184-b35f-3e3f-b74a-4137ef276673", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a45f8853a5f95e3760dfbd7ba09d3d597d247040 <b0bfaf0544d08d093d6211d7ef8816fb0b5b6c75"}, {"id": "1033d9a4-d1a9-3814-a9ee-4795b93bd0d7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.17.2"}, {"id": "2adba09e-9152-30ce-a550-d9b8aaf440d2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.16.19"}, {"id": "340a91a8-3af8-3ad4-a92c-4cb433db651f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4.20"}, {"id": "3ef43c9b-3c90-3dc4-a7d7-5e0a5283d62b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18"}, {"id": "9c7f5d1a-f92f-342e-8207-cfa461ee9587", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a45f8853a5f95e3760dfbd7ba09d3d597d247040 <0f517480d5888cd54487c5662ce4da95b30ad798"}, {"id": "addb2cdf-d36d-39f1-a986-ad015151d4d6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.33"